HEADWORD: Lombardic
<hw>Lom*bar"dic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to Lombardy of the Lombards.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lombardic alphabet</b></col>, <cd>the ancient alphabet
derived from the Roman, and employed in the manuscript of Italy.</cd> --
<col><b>Lombardic architecture</b></col>, <cd>the debased Roman style of
architecture as found in parts of Northern Italy.</cd> <au>F. G.
Lee.</au> <col><b>Lombardy poplar</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Poplar</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

